cs.SD, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE 

The paper is about speech recognition using convolutional neural networks, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning. The most likely sub-category is cs.SD (sound), followed by cs.CL (computation and language), as the paper deals with speech recognition. The use of neural networks also suggests that it could fall under cs.LG (machine learning), cs.AI (artificial intelligence), or cs.NE (neural and evolutionary computing).
